WEBVTT

00:04.960 --> 00:07.210
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.290 --> 00:09.800
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:09.880 --> 00:12.220
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.300 --> 00:15.180
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.260 --> 00:17.550
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.640 --> 00:20.720
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.810 --> 00:23.060
♪ I wanna stay with you ♪

00:23.140 --> 00:26.600
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:28.820 --> 00:32.740
♪♪

00:32.820 --> 00:33.860
Ding ding!

00:33.950 --> 00:35.740
Eggs and soldiers
coming right up.

00:35.820 --> 00:37.910
Get 'em while they're
toasty warm.

00:37.990 --> 00:40.080
Notice how I served
from the left this time?

00:40.160 --> 00:41.450
Heh-heh. Nice.

00:41.540 --> 00:43.500
A-thank you,
Jimjams.

00:45.420 --> 00:47.170
Ha --

00:47.250 --> 00:49.460
Huh -- Ugh.

00:49.540 --> 00:51.760
I can't eat my breakfast unless
someone is interrupting me.

00:51.840 --> 00:54.260
Which one of the cabin creatures
hasn't interrupted me yet?

00:54.340 --> 00:55.590
Uh...

00:55.680 --> 00:57.340
Lem.

00:57.430 --> 00:58.510
Lem!

00:58.600 --> 01:01.140
I know
you're out there!

01:01.220 --> 01:02.270
Lem!

01:02.350 --> 01:03.930
[ Echoing ] Lem! Lem! Lem!

01:04.020 --> 01:04.930
[ Whispering ]
Alexa!

01:05.020 --> 01:07.440
Hi, Lem.
Susie's summoning me.

01:07.520 --> 01:08.810
Do you think
she found out?

01:08.900 --> 01:10.480
About
you-know-what?

01:10.570 --> 01:12.530
I don't think she knows,
but I told you

01:12.610 --> 01:13.990
this was going to
catch up with you.

01:14.070 --> 01:15.150
Remember?

01:15.240 --> 01:18.280
♪♪

01:18.360 --> 01:20.620
Hmm.

01:20.700 --> 01:21.870
What's this?

01:21.950 --> 01:24.250
It's an invitation
to a summer camp island.

01:24.330 --> 01:25.710
For both of us?

01:25.790 --> 01:28.000
Uh, nope.
Just me.

01:28.080 --> 01:29.290
Mm!

01:29.380 --> 01:31.800
[ Muffled radio broadcast ]

01:31.880 --> 01:33.420
What are you doing,
Lem?

01:33.510 --> 01:34.670
Nothing.

01:34.760 --> 01:36.800
Are you trying to make
a counterfeit invitation

01:36.880 --> 01:38.050
to that summer camp?

01:38.130 --> 01:42.470
It's not a counterfeit.
It's a facsimile.

01:42.560 --> 01:44.220
This looks like
a ransom note.

01:44.310 --> 01:45.980
And smells like --
[ Sniff! ]

01:46.060 --> 01:47.140
a belly button.

01:47.230 --> 01:49.310
No one will know
the difference.

01:49.400 --> 01:50.940
Plus, I'm five.

01:51.020 --> 01:54.400
Well, when this backfires,
which it most certainly will,

01:54.480 --> 01:56.490
don't come crawling to me
begging for help.

01:56.570 --> 02:00.160
Ha-ha-ha
ha-ha-ha-ha...

02:00.240 --> 02:03.200
[ Crying ]

02:03.280 --> 02:06.040
Please!
Please help me.

02:06.120 --> 02:08.870
Look, Lem, I just found out
my magical identity,

02:08.960 --> 02:10.880
and I don't need
this added complication

02:10.960 --> 02:12.130
in my life
right now.

02:12.210 --> 02:13.500
You made your
trundle bed.

02:13.590 --> 02:15.420
Now lie in it.

02:15.510 --> 02:19.930
It's not my fault that
I'm amazing at forgery!

02:20.010 --> 02:22.180
Susie: Lem!

02:22.260 --> 02:23.890
Ahh. Ahh!

02:23.970 --> 02:26.270
[ Gasp! ] Hedgehog!

02:26.350 --> 02:29.230
Hedgehog's really nice,
and she's smart!

02:29.310 --> 02:31.900
She'll know what to do!

02:31.980 --> 02:34.860
Do you have any other
favorite birds, Mr. Assistant?

02:34.940 --> 02:36.900
Uh, a toucan?

02:36.990 --> 02:38.280
Toucan...

02:38.360 --> 02:39.860
Yucatan...

02:39.950 --> 02:43.910
and tuna can...

02:43.990 --> 02:44.950
toucan!

02:45.030 --> 02:47.120
[ Laughs ] More!

02:47.200 --> 02:50.370
Hedgehog! I--ooh.

02:50.460 --> 02:51.830
I need your help.

02:51.920 --> 02:53.040
What's happening,
Lem?

02:53.130 --> 02:55.880
It's, well...

02:55.960 --> 02:58.050
I forged a letter
to get into summer camp,

02:58.130 --> 03:00.430
and now I'm trying
to avoid Susie.

03:00.510 --> 03:03.050
Whoa, scandalous!

03:03.140 --> 03:04.760
You should go hide
in Frozen Time.

03:04.850 --> 03:05.890
Susie can't
go there.

03:05.970 --> 03:07.310
'Cause she's immortal.

03:07.390 --> 03:09.060
In Frozen Time, you can
hang out with Ramona.

03:09.140 --> 03:10.480
She'll be able to
help you.

03:10.560 --> 03:11.940
Great!

03:12.020 --> 03:13.400
How do I get there?

03:13.480 --> 03:15.940
For starters, you'll need to
get ahold of a moon rock,

03:16.020 --> 03:18.360
and that's
a logistical nightmare.

03:18.440 --> 03:19.990
You'll have to go
visit the moon,

03:20.070 --> 03:21.910
but you don't want to ask him
for a moon rock straight up.

03:21.990 --> 03:23.410
That would
be impolite.

03:23.490 --> 03:25.580
I think you should take the moon
a friendship bracelet.

03:25.660 --> 03:27.700
Here's a moon rock.
Oh!

03:27.790 --> 03:30.870
For solo travel, hold the rock
between your hoof and your hand.

03:30.960 --> 03:34.710
Wait! I wanna get into
a good freeze pose.

03:34.790 --> 03:38.340
Wait wait, I have
a good freeze pose, too.

03:38.420 --> 03:39.420
Okay!

03:39.510 --> 03:41.590
[ Cluck! ]

03:41.670 --> 03:43.260
[ Cluck! ]
Aahh...

03:43.340 --> 03:47.470
[ Slow-mo ]
choooo!

03:47.560 --> 03:48.890
Wow.

03:52.560 --> 03:56.310
Wooow.

03:56.400 --> 03:57.360
[ Humming ]

03:57.440 --> 03:58.610
[ Knock on door ]

03:58.690 --> 04:00.320
[ Chirp! ]

04:00.400 --> 04:01.950
Now,
who could it be?

04:02.030 --> 04:03.700
Ah-ah.

04:03.780 --> 04:05.820
Do I recognize you,
sweetie?

04:05.910 --> 04:08.080
Hi, I'm Lem.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.450
I'm on the lam.

04:09.540 --> 04:10.910
From whom?

04:11.000 --> 04:12.410
Susie.

04:12.500 --> 04:13.620
Why?

04:13.710 --> 04:15.960
Because I smuggled myself
into the camp.

04:16.040 --> 04:19.210
Ah, say no more.

04:19.300 --> 04:21.460
And have you no one else
to help you, poppet?

04:21.550 --> 04:23.260
Well, my sister's
kinda busy

04:23.340 --> 04:25.840
with her whole
magical identity thing,

04:25.930 --> 04:29.010
and seeing as how I don't
have a magical identity,

04:29.100 --> 04:32.850
I'll never be busy,
but I will be in trouble.

04:32.930 --> 04:37.110
Do you have any small,
breathable hidey holes?
Hmm.

04:37.190 --> 04:41.820
Yes, I have hidey holes aplenty
and crawl spaces galore!

04:41.900 --> 04:46.950
But first things first.
You'll need a disguise.

04:47.030 --> 04:48.450
Lem?
Yes?

04:48.530 --> 04:51.370
Your name
isn't Lem anymore.

04:51.450 --> 04:55.120
It's Fuzzy Pink Time Baby
Number 1118.

04:55.210 --> 04:56.080
Catchy.

04:56.170 --> 04:58.130
Now you can
roam freely!

04:58.210 --> 05:02.130
Can we roam into the kitchen
and roam up a little snack?

05:02.210 --> 05:04.170
I'm starving.

05:04.260 --> 05:06.720
Do you like
bubble and squeak?

05:06.800 --> 05:10.180
Are there any other food
dishes that evoke onomatopoeia?

05:10.260 --> 05:11.510
I like the bubbles.

05:11.600 --> 05:13.390
I like the squeak.

05:13.470 --> 05:14.930
Being on the lam
is great.

05:15.020 --> 05:17.020
[ Growl! ]

05:17.100 --> 05:19.020
Ahh.

05:19.110 --> 05:20.060
[ Growl! ]

05:20.150 --> 05:23.900
[ Squeak! ]

05:23.990 --> 05:25.570
W-What's going on?

05:25.650 --> 05:26.700
[ Gasp! ] Oh, no!

05:26.780 --> 05:29.320
Susie found me!

05:29.410 --> 05:31.700
Oh, dear,
it's not Susie.

05:31.780 --> 05:33.870
Quickly,
into the Jabber-bunker!

05:33.950 --> 05:39.170
♪♪

05:39.250 --> 05:40.880
[ Roar! ]

05:40.960 --> 05:42.000
What is it?

05:42.090 --> 05:43.670
The fearsome
Jabberwock.

05:43.760 --> 05:46.550
He knows you're not supposed
to be in Frozen Time.

05:46.630 --> 05:48.380
[ Screech! ]

05:48.470 --> 05:50.550
Well,
what do I do?

05:50.640 --> 05:52.970
Well, probably
what I had to do

05:53.060 --> 05:55.560
when I first
came to Frozen Time.

05:55.640 --> 05:57.690
I stayed in the house
for 15 years,

05:57.770 --> 06:00.190
a lot of that time
spent down in this bunker

06:00.270 --> 06:02.400
while the Jabberwock
got acquainted with me.

06:02.480 --> 06:06.070
It's like letting a dog
get used to a new scent.

06:06.150 --> 06:07.240
[ Growl! ]

06:07.320 --> 06:09.530
Oh! Oh!

06:09.610 --> 06:11.160
Quickly,
Time Baby 1118!

06:11.240 --> 06:13.580
He can smell you!
Close the window!

06:13.660 --> 06:18.080
[ Roar! ]

06:18.160 --> 06:20.080
Don't fret,
little time baby.

06:20.170 --> 06:22.210
You'll be really scared
for about,

06:22.290 --> 06:23.460
oh, 5 or 10 years,

06:23.540 --> 06:26.210
but--but then, you'll
get used to it.

06:26.300 --> 06:29.050
That sounds...
long.

06:29.130 --> 06:30.380
[ Growl! ]

06:30.470 --> 06:33.100
Mm.
Longer than you think.

06:33.180 --> 06:35.390
♪♪

06:35.470 --> 06:36.930
Lady, I don't
want to tell you

06:37.020 --> 06:38.730
how to outfit
your Jabber-bunker,

06:38.810 --> 06:41.940
but do you have a deck
of cards, or something?

06:42.020 --> 06:44.480
Frozen Time
is starting to drag.

06:44.570 --> 06:48.950
Oh, unfortunately, I don't have
a deck of cards or anything.

06:49.030 --> 06:52.120
You see, the Jabberwock
can smell levity.

06:52.200 --> 06:55.450
I do know something you can
do to pass the time.

06:55.540 --> 06:58.250
Yes! Anything.
<i>Please.</i>

06:58.330 --> 07:01.120
You can write a goodbye letter
to your sister.

07:01.210 --> 07:02.960
Uh...goodbye?

07:03.040 --> 07:07.800
Well, you're not going to be
able to see her again.

07:07.880 --> 07:09.010
Hmm.

07:09.090 --> 07:11.550
I don't even know
where to start.

07:11.630 --> 07:13.640
Maybe start
by reflecting on

07:13.720 --> 07:16.510
the most fun
things you did together.

07:16.600 --> 07:19.060
♪♪

07:19.140 --> 07:20.310
Ohh!

07:20.390 --> 07:22.480
Uh...uh!

07:22.560 --> 07:24.110
Ahh!

07:24.190 --> 07:31.110
♪♪

07:31.200 --> 07:33.780
Ew, no!
Alexa, stop it! Ew!

07:33.870 --> 07:44.380
♪♪

07:44.460 --> 07:46.500
I can't live
without her!

07:46.590 --> 07:48.000
She's my
one and only!

07:48.090 --> 07:49.760
I can't
stay here!

07:49.840 --> 07:51.090
There, there.

07:51.170 --> 07:53.050
That's how it
should be, dear.

07:53.130 --> 07:55.760
I didn't want Susie
to kick me out for lying.
[ Growl! ]

07:55.850 --> 07:57.810
It's just not fair that
Alexa got invited

07:57.890 --> 08:02.140
[ Heavy footsteps thudding ]
and I didn't, just
because I'm not magical.

08:02.230 --> 08:03.770
[ Thudding fades ]

08:03.850 --> 08:05.940
[ Cheering ]

08:06.020 --> 08:08.690
Ah, the Jabberwock
has gone.

08:08.770 --> 08:10.690
Now let's go upstairs
and I can give you

08:10.780 --> 08:14.910
some inside info
about Susie's anger.

08:14.990 --> 08:17.410
You have every right
to be scared of Susie.

08:17.490 --> 08:19.330
She'll be livid
when she finds out

08:19.410 --> 08:20.910
you snuck onto
the island,

08:21.000 --> 08:23.540
but she'll get used to
the idea eventually

08:23.620 --> 08:24.960
and she'll
calm down.

08:25.040 --> 08:27.210
In the meantime,
I'll give you some things

08:27.290 --> 08:28.540
that will help
protect you from

08:28.630 --> 08:31.420
the first blast
of Susie's anger.

08:31.510 --> 08:34.380
Ramona: Here, take these magical
cuckoo clock pinecones.

08:34.470 --> 08:36.430
They make
good earplugs.

08:36.510 --> 08:39.390
They'll turn Susie's screams
into a silly, light cough.

08:39.470 --> 08:42.310
[ Giggle! ]
And, yes...

08:42.390 --> 08:44.560
Put these paperweights
in your pockets

08:44.640 --> 08:46.690
so if Susie stomps
around her cabin,

08:46.770 --> 08:48.310
shaking
the very foundations,

08:48.400 --> 08:50.480
you'll be able
to keep your balance.

08:50.570 --> 08:52.780
And for
a third thing --

08:52.860 --> 08:54.070
here's a pair
of old slippers

08:54.150 --> 08:56.280
that will make
your feet feel comfy

08:56.360 --> 08:58.740
even if the rest of you
is uncomfy.

08:58.820 --> 09:00.740
Susie won't notice
the slippers?

09:00.830 --> 09:03.410
She has a real blind spot
for footwear.

09:03.500 --> 09:10.540
♪♪

09:10.630 --> 09:13.550
Aww,
Susie looks good.

09:13.630 --> 09:15.930
Oh, she made
new curtains.

09:16.010 --> 09:17.640
I like those.

09:17.720 --> 09:20.930
But now, um, to get you out
of Frozen Time,

09:21.010 --> 09:24.350
take a glass of water,
add some salt to the water,

09:24.430 --> 09:26.190
and drop
the moon rock in there.

09:26.270 --> 09:27.400
[ Sparkle! ]

09:27.480 --> 09:29.440
Goodbye, Lem.

09:29.520 --> 09:32.110
Lem!

09:32.190 --> 09:33.650
Oh,
there you are.

09:33.730 --> 09:34.860
[ Sniff! Sniff! ]

09:34.940 --> 09:37.990
Why do you smell
like Ramona?

09:38.070 --> 09:39.870
I'm sorry --
wait.

09:39.950 --> 09:41.330
[ Grunt ]

09:41.410 --> 09:43.790
I'm sorry I snuck into
Summer Camp,

09:43.870 --> 09:48.120
especially because I don't have
a magical identity.

09:48.210 --> 09:50.380
Wait, what?
You did what?

09:50.460 --> 09:51.960
Do you know how much
trouble you're --

09:52.040 --> 09:53.670
Please don't yell
at Alexa!

09:53.750 --> 09:55.800
She had nothing
to do with it.

09:55.880 --> 09:57.630
I just wanted
to be near her.

09:57.720 --> 10:00.300
That's why I made
a forged invitation.

10:00.390 --> 10:02.510
Oh, this is
a sister thing?

10:02.600 --> 10:03.970
Okay.

10:04.060 --> 10:06.230
Not having a magical identity
is still an identity.

10:06.310 --> 10:07.810
Everyone has a place,
Lem.

10:07.890 --> 10:10.150
And, just because you don't
have a magical identity

10:10.230 --> 10:12.440
doesn't mean you can't
interrupt my breakfast.

10:12.520 --> 10:13.860
Care to join me?

10:15.440 --> 10:16.610
Here, these are cold.

10:16.690 --> 10:18.650
Another breakfast,
comin' up.

10:18.740 --> 10:21.320
Ramona says she likes
your curtains.

10:21.410 --> 10:23.740
So you were with Ramona!

10:26.160 --> 10:29.000
What else did she say about me?

10:29.080 --> 10:31.670
[ Jingle! ]

10:31.750 --> 10:33.000
[ Sigh! ]

10:33.090 --> 10:35.880
You can come out now,
my little actors.

10:35.960 --> 10:38.130
[ Chirp! ]

10:38.220 --> 10:39.840
Wonderful performance.

10:39.930 --> 10:44.060
Yup, I really believed you were
all scared of the Jabberwock.

10:44.140 --> 10:46.680
And I have great news,
my little babies.

10:46.770 --> 10:50.350
You've all been nominated
for British Acting Awards!

10:50.440 --> 10:52.360
[ Cheering! ]

10:52.440 --> 10:53.770
And that's not all!

10:53.860 --> 10:57.190
Big Baby has been nominated
for special effects!

10:57.280 --> 11:01.410
Great job shaking the house
and making terrifying noises!

11:01.490 --> 11:03.740
[ Giggles ]

11:03.820 --> 11:05.240
[ Growls ]

11:06.660 --> 11:12.380
♪♪

11:12.460 --> 11:18.050
♪♪

11:18.130 --> 11:20.630
Aww,
Susie looks good.
